<http://www.spektrix.com/gatewaytheatre/event/95401AGGBMPCTBRTDHHTVTLNKSQLNNNQC> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name " Acting A (Ages 8-10)";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Acting A</span><span><br/></span>Ages 8-10<span><br/></span>Sept 17, 2026 - April 15, 2027<span><br/></span>Thursdays,  5:00pm-6:30pm <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In Acting A, the first half of the year focuses on building ensemble, gaining familiarity and practice of skills, and advancing theatre learning through material and small projects. In December, each class will host an Open Studio on the last class before the holiday break, sharing the skills they have learned with invited friends and family.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In the second half of the year, skill development is augmented as students rehearse a story/play/musical in preparation for their year-end presentation. Students are assigned roles; they learn material and explore; work at home is expected, and extra attention to attendance is expected.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In April, students showcase their work in an in-class presentation to invited family and friends. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please note: All class withdrawals are subject to a 30% course withdrawal fee. View full <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.gatewaytheatre.com/gateway-academy-terms-conditions\">Refund/Cancellation Policy here</a>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-09-17T17:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
