<http://www.spektrix.com/gatewaytheatre/event/96201AVHBRLKVRBQDMRMKRTNNBPDVNJLH> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Musical Theatre Skills (Ages 11-18)";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Musical Theatre Skills</span><span><br/></span>Ages 11-18<span><br/></span>Sept 15, 2026 - Apr 13, 2027<span><br/></span>Tuesdays, 7:00pm-9:00pm <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Musical Theatre Skills is designed for students with all levels of experience who are interested in developing their theatrical toolbox.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The first half of the year will focus on ensemble and skill-building; in the second half of the year, students will apply what they’ve learned by rehearsing a short musical.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The year will culminate in an in-class presentation where students present the show without any added production elements (lights, costumes, etc). This will allow students to focus primarily on developing skills and gaining confidence, with a rigorous rehearsal process that works toward the final presentation for invited family and friends.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Students of this class will also be given access to dress rehearsal seats for Gateway’s Holiday musical and short talks by theatre professionals throughout the year.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please note: All class withdrawals are subject to a 30% course withdrawal fee. View full <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.gatewaytheatre.com/gateway-academy-terms-conditions\">Refund/Cancellation Policy here</a>
""";
